PROJECT 3: IMAGE CAPTIONING
Title

Simple Image Caption Generator Using C

Objective

To generate captions for images based on image names.

Description

Image Captioning combines image understanding and text generation. In this simplified project, predefined captions are displayed for specific image names.

Algorithm
Start program.
Accept image name.
Compare image name with predefined values.
Display matching caption.
End program.
Source Code
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>

int main()
{
    char image[50];

    printf("Enter Image Name: ");
    scanf("%s",image);

    if(strcmp(image,"dog.jpg")==0)
    {
        printf("Caption: A dog is standing on the grass.\n");
    }
    else if(strcmp(image,"cat.jpg")==0)
    {
        printf("Caption: A cat is sitting on a chair.\n");
    }
    else if(strcmp(image,"car.jpg")==0)
    {
        printf("Caption: A car is parked on the road.\n");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("Caption: Unknown Image.\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
Sample Input
dog.jpg
Sample Output
Caption: A dog is standing on the grass.
Sample Input
cat.jpg
Sample Output
Caption: A cat is sitting on a chair.
Result

The Image Captioning system successfully generated captions for predefined images.
